properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS -  Wollongong Education Precinct - WOLLONGONG Princes Motorway, Memorial Drive at University of Wollongong
properties.adviceB: Use diversions; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 Princes Mwy southbound traffic exiting at University Ave will be diverted left to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine St will diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists wishing to access the M1 Princes Mwy northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Ave will be diverted via Murphys Ave and Robsons Rd.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow instructions of traffic controllers.

properties.otherAdvice:
Road closed to the general public until further notice due to damage to the road, pavement, fallen trees, and water over the road.

Access to Kangaroo Valley/Barrengarry is permitted to emergency services/local residents/local shop owners â€“ businesses/delivery drivers/special and â€“ or major events staff or venue attendees.

Please note the advised route heading into Kangaroo Valley/Barrengarry is via Fitzroy Falls closure point at Nowra Rd and May Vale Rd. Motorists are advised to exercise caution when accessing the area.

Access to Kangaroo Valley Rd and or Woodhill Mountain Rd/Wattamolla Rd is also closed due to road damage, fallen trees and water over road.

Road is only accessible to emergency services, local residents, delivery drives with small vehicles up to 4T.

All other required access into Kangaroo Valley/Barrengarry from the Berry Mountain end is to be accessed via Fitzroy Falls at closure point of Nowra Rd and May Vale Rd.

Emergency services are advised to use caution when responding via Kangaroo Valley Rd and or Woodhill Mountain/Wattamolla Rd due to poor road conditions.

Roadwork is currently being undertaken on Moss Vale Rd â€“ Cambewarra Mountain to restore and reopen the road as quickly as possible.
